cerentIfExtMIB.name: cerentIfExtMIB
cerentIfExtMIB.contactinfo: support@Cisco.com Postal: Cisco Systems 1450 N. McDowell Blvd. Petaluma, CA 94954 USA Tel: +1-877-323-7368
cerentIfExtMIB.description: This module defines objects for managing interfaces.

cerentIfExtTable.name: cerentIfExtTable
cerentIfExtTable.description: This table contains one row per interface.

cerentIfExtPreServiceAlarmSuppression.name: cerentIfExtPreServiceAlarmSuppression
cerentIfExtPreServiceAlarmSuppression.description: This object can be set through a management interface. When the administrative state of this interface is 'down', the value of this object does not have any impact. When the administrative state of this interface is 'up', if this object has a value of 'false', an alarm on this interface will be reported. If the value of this object is 'true' then all alarms on this interface will be suppressed. If the interface has a good signal, the soak timer will be started, if the port is faulted before the soak timer expires, the soak timer will be reset to the provisioned maximum value. If the soak timer expires then the value of this object is automatically set to 'false'.

cerentIfExtConfiguredSoakTime.name: cerentIfExtConfiguredSoakTime
cerentIfExtConfiguredSoakTime.description: This is the configured maximum value of the soak timer for this interface.

cerentIfExtCurrentSoakTime.name: cerentIfExtCurrentSoakTime
cerentIfExtCurrentSoakTime.description: This is the current value of the soak timer for this interface. The difference between cerntIfExtConfiguredSoakTime and this object gives the time duration for which this interface has had a good signal.

cerentIfExtMIBCompliance.name: cerentIfExtMIBCompliance
cerentIfExtMIBCompliance.description: Describes the requirements for conformance to the High Capacity Media Independent Group.

cerentIfExtGroup.name: cerentIfExtGroup
cerentIfExtGroup.description: The objects for storing all the current alarm thresholds
